The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Thursday, September 05, 2002  Good Morning Hello It's Thursday, September 5, 2002				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Southern Avenue. Work is in progress on the drainage pumping station.				 																																	A portion of the northern flank of AJC Bose Road and JL Nehru Road will be closed. 				 																Harmony march				 																																	A harmony march, organised by Bangiya Christiya Pariseba as a homage to Mother Teresa, will start at 3 pm from Mathkol, Dum Dum, and converge on Mall Road.				 																Magic of rhythm				 																																	Bollywood Dreams, presented by Padatik Contemporary Dance Centre, at Kala Mandir at 6.30 pm.				 																Fabrics on display				 																																	An exhibition of fabrics and textiles, presented by Crafts Council of West Bengal, at Obsession Gallery, from 10 am to 7.30 pm.				 																																	A display of Dastakar Andhras handloom products, presented by Sasha, at 27, Mirza Ghalib Street.				 																																	Tanushree Shankar will inaugurate an exhibition of designerwear at Anchor furniture shop, Swabhumi, at 4 pm.
